Subject: [PATCH] Fix cmake_minimum_required for CMake 4.x compatibility

CMake 4.x removed compatibility with cmake_minimum_required < 3.5.
Update to 3.5 to fix build with newer CMake versions.

---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -26,7 +26,7 @@
 # (INCLUDING NEGLIGENCE OR OTHERWISE) ARISING IN ANY WAY OUT OF THE USE
 # OF THIS SOFTWARE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGE.

-cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.1)
+cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.5)
 project(Snappy VERSION 1.2.1 LANGUAGES C CXX)

 # C++ standard can be overridden when this is used as a sub-project.
